{"warnings":{"parse":{"*":"The value passed for \"page\" contains invalid or non-normalized data. Textual data should be valid, NFC-normalized Unicode without C0 control characters other than HT (\\t), LF (\\n), and CR (\\r)."}},"parse":{"title":"\u00c1lvaro Arias","pageid":48749973,"revid":757138556,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>\u00c1lvaro Arias</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (Oviedo, Spain, 1969) is a Linguist and Hispanist specialist in the fields of <a href=\"/wiki/Phonology\" title=\"Phonology\">Phonology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Morphology_(linguistics)\" title=\"Morphology (linguistics)\">Morphology</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Dialectology\" title=\"Dialectology\">Dialectology</a>. He has more than thirty scholarly publications. </p><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg/220px-Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"313\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg/330px-Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg/440px-Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"842\" data-file-height=\"1199\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portada_del_libro_Oposici%C3%B3n_y_pertinencia_de_%C3%81lvaro_Arias.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Cover of \u00c1lvaro Arias's book \"Oposici\u00f3n y pertinencia en Ling\u00fc\u00edstica\"</div></div></div>\n<p>Born in <a href=\"/wiki/Oviedo\" title=\"Oviedo\">Oviedo</a>, with family roots in Felechosa (<a href=\"/wiki/Aller,_Asturias\" title=\"Aller, Asturias\">Aller, Asturias</a>), is a Linguist<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and Hispanist.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He was educated at University of Oviedo, where he received a BA in Spanish Philology and a PhD in Spanish Linguistics.\n</p><p>He is professor of Spanish <a href=\"/wiki/Philology\" title=\"Philology\">Philology</a> at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oviedo\" title=\"University of Oviedo\">University of Oviedo</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and author of publications on <a href=\"/wiki/Phonology\" title=\"Phonology\">Phonology</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Grammar\" title=\"Grammar\">Grammar</a>, from a theoretical and dialectal perspective, with special attention to the <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_language\" title=\"Spanish language\">Spanish</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Galician_language\" title=\"Galician language\">Galician</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Asturian_language\" title=\"Asturian language\">Asturian</a> languages. He has published over 30 articles and book chapters, and edited or authored several books, in these areas.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He has also published studies of linguistic historiography<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and rescued and published literature in Asturian of the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Damaso Alonso Prize of Philological Research,<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> he has also received other awards for his academic work.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=%C3%81lvaro_Arias&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Full name in Spanish transcription: \u00c1lvaro Arias Cabal; complete name: \u00c1lvaro Arias-Cachero Cabal.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://linguistlist.org/people/personal/get-personal-page2.cfm?PersonID=173668\">The Linguist list: \u00c1lvaro Arias.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://hispanismo.cervantes.es/Hispanistas_ficha.asp?DOCN=12433\">Portal del Hispanismo: \u00c1lvaro Arias.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://filoesp.uniovi.es/personal/pdi\">Website of the Department of Spanish Philology at the University of Oviedo.</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Arias, \u00c1lvaro (1999). <i>El morfema de \u2018neutro de materia\u2019 en asturiano</i>. Universidade de Santiago de Compostela.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=El+morfema+de+%E2%80%98neutro+de+materia%E2%80%99+en+asturiano&amp;rft.pub=Universidade+de+Santiago+de+Compostela&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.aulast=Arias&amp;rft.aufirst=%C3%81lvaro&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A%C3%81lvaro+Arias\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Arias, \u00c1lvaro (2000). <i>Oposici\u00f3n y pertinencia en Ling\u00fc\u00edstica</i>. Universidad de Oviedo.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Oposici%C3%B3n+y+pertinencia+en+Ling%C3%BC%C3%ADstica&amp;rft.pub=Universidad+de+Oviedo&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.aulast=Arias&amp;rft.aufirst=%C3%81lvaro&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A%C3%81lvaro+Arias\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Julio Somoza: <i>Primer ensayo de un vocabulario bable (1891~1901).</i> Critical edition of \u00c1lvaro Arias, Uvi\u00e9u: Academia de la Llingua Asturiana, 1996.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Juan Gonz\u00e1lez Villar: <i>La Judit (